Teriyaki Chicken Bowl

Combine ingredients in a small bowl to make teriyaki sauce.
&
1 tablespoon sugar
1 tablespoon soy sauce
1 tablespoon mirin
1 tablespoon sake
&&&

Cut chicken into bit-sized pieces and sprinkle with salt
&
12.4 oz (350 g) boneless chicken
1/4 tsp salt
&&&

Heat pan on medium high heat. If the chicken is skinless, add oil.
Add chicken onto pan in single layer.

&&&

Let chicken fry until browned on one side. Flip and brown the other side.

&&&

Stir the teriyaki sauce and add it to thepan.

&&&

Let the mixture boil, tossing the chicken until the sauce forms a thick, shiny glaze.

&&&

Serve on rice, drizzling with remaining sauce, and then top with boiled peas.
&
2 bowls cooked rice
1/3 cup peas
&&&
